page.title: 09FISH
page.content: Carp are found in weedy and lily infested water,these are big fish that grow up to two feet long and eat the weed from these pools that have little flow to clean them. Eels are found in the mud pools shallows of marshy ground or streams.These are sometimes eaten in jelly or in a pie.They have been known to find their way into trout pools through cleanage pipes. Roach,pike,dace and bream are found in the rivers they are only small because they leave for bigger rivers when they are older. As well as all the fish that have been mentioned,the marshland,rivers, streams and the muddy patches of our area have got life in them.These places are where amphibious creatures such as toads,newts and frogs live.
